            . I am the wife of Abraham Hart, who is a <rs id="t18170115-214-viclabel1158" type="occupation">glass-cutter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170115-214-victim1492 t18170115-214-viclabel1158"></join>. On the 20th of January, about six o'clock in the evening; I was going to Spital-fields, the prisoner spoke to me several times; and when I came to <placeName id="t18170115-214-crimeloc1159">Sun-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170115-214-crimeloc1159" type="placeName" value="Sun-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170115-214-crimeloc1159" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170115-214-off1156 t18170115-214-crimeloc1159"></join>, he took my bundle from me, and ran away; I followed him, and called stop thief! he was stopped before I lost sight of him, he dropped the bundle. I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>ABRAHAM OAKLEY. I am a plasterer. I heard the alarm; I saw the prisoner drop the bundle. I took it up, and secured him.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
